Bleep watches ui source code and linked modules and triggers builds on code changes.

Modify 'bleep.config.json' to tweak log format, turn off colors, or change default arguments.  If you don't want to build & watch css, set "gulp" to false.

Specify one or more modules as arguments to build & watch them and their dependencies. Specify no modules to only run typescript watches (no rollups). The "defaultArgs" property in bleep.config.json defines a default argument list for bleep. It defaults to ["all"] which builds everything.
